are talking
about are paltry.

19:55.461 --> 20:01.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So what would happen is, if you
skip some
time and go without coverage
because you can't

20:01.200 --> 20:05.471 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
afford it, you can't afford the
premium, what
some of these proposals would do
would effectively

20:05.504 --> 20:10.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
lock you out until you either
get back into
an employer-based plan or become
eligible

20:10.276 --> 20:12.178 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for Medicare.

20:12.211 --> 20:14.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right,
this is a conversation,
and legislation will eventually
make its way

20:14.814 --> 20:15.781 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to Capitol Hill.

20:15.815 --> 20:16.882 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We will have you back then.

20:16.916 --> 20:21.720 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Robert Moffit, Sabrina Corlette,
thank you
both.

20:21.754 --> 20:24.156 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ROBERT MOFFIT: Pleasure.

20:24.190 --> 20:27.460 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SABRINA CORLETTE: Thank you.

20:27.493 --> 20:30.763 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It was a pleasure.

20:30.796 --> 20:34.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ROBERT MOFFIT: All right.

20:34.066 --> 20:39.672 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Overseas now:
Thousands
more civilians fled the eastern
rebel-held

20:39.705 --> 20:45.077 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sectors of Syria's largest city,
Aleppo, this
week, as the war there took an
even more violent

20:45.111 --> 20:46.879 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
turn.

20:46.912 --> 20:49.849 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Syrian Civil Defense Rescue
Group reported
that at least 50 people were
killed today

20:49.882 --> 20:54.687 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and 150 injured, amid relentless
shelling
and bombing.

20:54.720 --> 20:57.356 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Chief foreign affairs
correspondent Margaret
Warner reports.

20:57.389 --> 21:03.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: In the last few
days, Syrian
government forces have retaken a
large swathe

21:03.062 --> 21:08.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of Eastern Aleppo, long a
stronghold for fighters
opposed to President Bashar
al-Assad.

21:08.501 --> 21:15.374 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Aid groups say shortages of food
and medical
care there are the gravest yet.

21:15.407 --> 21:18.744 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
QUESTION (through translator):
How did your
mother die?

21:18.777 --> 21:21.280 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator): She
died of hunger.

21:21.313 --> 21:23.949 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We haven't had any water or food
for five
months.

21:23.983 --> 21:25.284 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They didn't feed us.

21:25.317 --> 21:27.720 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They ate bread, and we were
hungry.

21:27.753 --> 21:33.359 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: As the death
toll keeps mounting,
the top U.N. envoy to Syria
suggested today

21:33.392 --> 21:36.095 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the rebels may not be able to
hold out.

21:36.128 --> 21:40.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STAFFAN DE MISTURA, Special
United Nations
Envoy for Syria: This is a
military acceleration,

21:40.132 --> 21:43.235 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and I can't tell you how long
Eastern Aleppo
will last.

21:43.269 --> 21:48.274 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Major aid
groups are still
being denied entry to help
civilians remaining

21:48.307 --> 21:50.176 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the city.

21:50.209 --> 21:52.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BETTINA LUESCHER, World Food
Program: We are
ready to mobilize food,
preposition in warehouses

21:52.244 --> 21:59.451 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in Western Aleppo, or across the
border from
Turkey, to the people trapped in
Eastern Aleppo,

21:59.485 --> 22:01.120 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
if access is granted.

22:01.153 --> 22:06.825 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, once again, we join -- like
everybody
else, let us get into Eastern
Aleppo.

22:06.859 --> 22:08.561 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We can help the people there.

22:08.594 --> 22:10.262 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Let us in.

22:10.296 --> 22:14.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: There is not a
single working
hospital left in East Aleppo
either.

22:14.900 --> 22:19.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: Medical structures that we
have been
supporting for many years that
have been bombed

22:19.038 --> 22:23.375 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
now almost a dozen times over
the last year.

22:23.409 --> 22:25.244 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's just incredible.

22:25.277 --> 22:28.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: And Russian and
Syrian planes
reportedly have dropped leaflets
on East Aleppo,

22:28.814 --> 22:34.220 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
warning: "If you do not leave
these areas
urgently, you will be
annihilated.

22:34.253 --> 22:36.889 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You know that everyone has given
up on you.

22:36.922 --> 22:38.891 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They left you alone to face your
doom."

22:38.924 --> 22:41.760 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RANIA ABOUZEID, Journalist: You
know, the
Syrian rebels have always felt
abandoned.

22:41.794 --> 22:47.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Journalist
Rania Abouzeid
in Beirut keeps in contact with
Western-backed

22:47.132 --> 22:48.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
rebel commanders.

22:48.901 --> 22:52.471 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RANIA ABOUZEID: They felt
abandoned by an
international community that
said Assad must

22:52.504 --> 22:55.708 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
go, but didn't really help them
to see that
through.

22:55.741 --> 23:00.346 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So there's a great sense of
abandonment, there
is a sense of anger.

23:00.379 --> 23:05.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: The battlefield
tilted sharply
in Assad's favor when Russia
entered the war

23:05.417 --> 23:07.152 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
14 months ago.

23:07.186 --> 23:12.658 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With Russian airpower, and
Shiite militias
from Iran, Lebanon and Iraq on
the ground,

23:12.691 --> 23:15.928 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Assad regime has regained
its footing
and territory.

23:15.961 --> 23:20.499 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RANIA ABOUZEID: We have seen
several instances
in the recent past, over the
past year, when

23:20.532 --> 23:28.440 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it looked like Aleppo might
fall, but certainly
nothing in terms of the scale
and the speed

23:28.474 --> 23:33.946 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
at which we have seen regime
gains in the
eastern part of the city over
the past 24

23:33.979 --> 23:35.781 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to 48 hours.

23:35.814 --> 23:40.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So it certainly looks like this
might be the
decisive moment for the future
of rebel-held

23:40.953 --> 23:42.755 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Aleppo at this point.

23:42.788 --> 23:47.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Secretary of
State John Kerry
keeps pushing for a cease-fire
for Aleppo,

23:47.059 --> 23:51.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
negotiating with Russia and
regional powers
backing different rebel
factions.

23:51.297 --> 23:55.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RANIA ABOUZEID: The Syrians have
some hope
that if the bigger guys, the
bigger players

23:55.167 --> 23:56.969 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
can find some sort of agreement.

23:57.002 --> 24:00.773 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then perhaps that might trickle
down to mean
something in terms of the
battlefield on the

24:00.806 --> 24:02.508 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
ground.

24:02.541 --> 24:05.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: But other top
Obama officials
suspect Russia wants to cement a
military

24:05.944 --> 24:10.249 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
victory on the ground now, in
the administration's
final weeks.

24:10.282 --> 24:15.020 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Said one: "If you're sitting in
Moscow, would
you rather deal with President
Obama, or present

24:15.054 --> 24:18.257 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a fait accompli to new President
Trump?"

24:18.290 --> 24:22.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For now, it looks like the
rebels want to
fight on in Aleppo.

24:22.494 --> 24:25.064 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RANIA ABOUZEID: Well, certainly
the rebels
will try and win it back.

24:25.097 --> 24:28.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the question is, will they
have the means
to do that?

24:28.200 --> 24:30.536 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Will they have the international
support to
do that?

24:30.569 --> 24:35.274 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And will this change anything in
terms of
the calculus of their
international backers?

24:35.307 --> 24:39.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Questions that
will have
to be faced by Syria, its
neighbors and the

24:39.611 --> 24:41.780 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
new American president alike.

24:41.814 --> 24:49.355 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Margaret Warner
in Washington.

24:49.388 --> 24:58.464 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Stay with us.

24:58.497 --> 25:03.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour":
economic ties
between the U.S. and Mexico
under a President

25:03.702 --> 25:07.773 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trump; and athletes who are
having an impact
off the field.

25:07.806 --> 25:13.612 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But first: the battle over
school choice and
public education is likely to
intensify under

25:13.645 --> 25:15.414 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the Trump administration.

25:15.447 --> 25:19.818 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
His choice for education
secretary, Betsy
DeVos, is a big supporter of
vouchers and

25:19.852 --> 25:24.456 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
charter schools, both of which
use tax dollars
that would normally go to
neighborhood public

25:24.490 --> 25:26.225 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
schools.

25:26.258 --> 25:29.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The fight over these issues is
already building
within the African-American
community.

25:29.995 --> 25:35.401 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The NAACP is calling for a
moratorium on new
charter schools, but some black
parents are

25:35.434 --> 25:37.469 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
pushing back against that.

25:37.503 --> 25:41.573 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent Lisa Stark
of our partner
Education Week reports from
Memphis, part

25:41.607 --> 25:44.510 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of our weekly series Making the
Grade.

25:44.543 --> 25:53.085 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA STARK: At Freedom
Preparatory Academy
in Memphis, there's a constant
beat echoing

25:53.118 --> 25:56.455 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
through the hallways.

25:56.488 --> 26:04.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
