African drum class
required of every middle
schooler here.

26:04.129 --> 26:11.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What's being drummed into these
charter school
students is that education, a
college degree

26:11.904 --> 26:20.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and proper behavior are critical
to getting
ahead.

26:20.212 --> 26:23.849 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If I ask you to describe Freedom
Prep in one
word, what would it be?

26:23.882 --> 26:24.850 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TYLER VAUGHN, Student: College.

26:24.883 --> 26:25.851 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
BRIANNA TODD, Student:
Preparation.

26:25.884 --> 26:27.686 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TALY ORDONEZ, Student: Life.

26:27.719 --> 26:31.323 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: Senior Tyler Vaughn,
eighth grader
Brianna Todd and fifth grader
Taly Ordonez

26:31.356 --> 26:35.761 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
all came to Freedom Prep after
stints in traditional
public schools.

26:35.794 --> 26:40.732 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TYLER VAUGHN: Since sixth grade,
they always
instilled in us that we would be
going to

26:40.766 --> 26:42.534 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
college and we would excel in
college.

26:42.568 --> 26:46.205 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRIANNA TODD: It definitely
teaches us to
be responsible throughout out
entire life.

26:46.238 --> 26:51.844 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TALY ORDONEZ: Charter school, it
prepares
you for college and life.

26:51.877 --> 26:57.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: Nearly three million
students
in the U.S. attend charter
schools in 42 states

26:57.349 --> 27:03.422 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and the District of Columbia,
about 6 percent
of all public school students
nationwide.

27:03.455 --> 27:08.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But in more than a dozen cities,
at least
30 percent of the students
attend charters.

27:08.660 --> 27:13.665 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
As in many cities,
African-American parents
in Memphis are voting with their
feet.

27:13.699 --> 27:18.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This was a struggling elementary
school three
years ago, when the state asked
Freedom Prep

27:18.770 --> 27:19.938 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to take it over.

27:19.972 --> 27:21.740 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The charter school came in.

27:21.773 --> 27:26.645 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Enrollment doubled.

27:26.678 --> 27:32.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Charter schools are often open
in poor neighborhoods,
and predominantly serve children
of color.

27:32.050 --> 27:33.852 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And they have a mixed record.

27:33.886 --> 27:35.120 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Some are excellent.

27:35.153 --> 27:37.222 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Others fall far short.

27:37.256 --> 27:40.225 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Some states have strict
standards for charters.

27:40.259 --> 27:41.994 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Others do not.

27:42.027 --> 27:44.663 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CORNELL WILLIAM BROOKS,
President, NAACP:
The issue for us is just simply
making sure

27:44.696 --> 27:46.465 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
everyone operates by the same
rules.

27:46.498 --> 27:52.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: The NAACP is calling
for a moratorium
on new charter schools,
concerned about a

27:52.771 --> 27:58.410 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
host of issues, including
charters that seem
to cherry-pick students or have
high suspension

27:58.443 --> 28:00.712 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
rates for children of color.

28:00.746 --> 28:02.447 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The group wants reforms.

28:02.481 --> 28:06.418 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CORNELL WILLIAM BROOKS: Make
sure kids aren't
being suspended or expelled
unfairly.

28:06.451 --> 28:12.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Make sure you have standards of
accountability
and transparency, and let's make
sure that

28:12.291 --> 28:18.063 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
we don't cream the best
students, to the disservice
of all the students.

28:18.096 --> 28:24.369 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: NAACP President
Cornell William
Brooks insists the group is not
anti-charter,

28:24.403 --> 28:30.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
